It should return the Azure App IP or hostname.

ğŸ› ï¸ Step-by-Step: Azure Private DNS Setup
ğŸ“Œ Step 1: Create Private DNS Zone
bash
Copy
Edit
az network private-dns zone create \
  --resource-group myResourceGroup \
  --name myapp.internal
ğŸ“Œ Step 2: Link it to a Virtual Network
bash
Copy
Edit
az network private-dns link vnet create \
  --resource-group myResourceGroup \
  --zone-name myapp.internal \
  --name link-to-vnet \
  --virtual-network myVNet \
  --registration-enabled true
ğŸ“Œ Step 3: Add A Record (Internal VM)
bash
Copy
Edit
az network private-dns record-set a add-record \
  --zone-name myapp.internal \
  --resource-group myResourceGroup \
  --record-set-name web \
  --ipv4-address 10.0.1.4
âœ… Now internal VMs in the VNet can access web.myapp.internal

ğŸ” Bonus: Use Azure DNS with App Services or Front Door
App Service + Custom Domain: Bind domain in "Custom domains"

Front Door + Custom Domain: Point www.domain.com to Front Door endpoint

